        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3961585992" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1318654566581077534">2.5 STARS<br/><br/>&quot;Her worst nightmare is realized and she finds herself on the run with her two young children, no money, and no plan.&quot; While this did happen in the book, there&apos;s a lot that happened before this, and even more story that happens after. Jillian herself is drawn fairly realistically. She isn&apos;t perfect, she&apos;s selfish at times, she doesn&apos;t always put her kids first. It made her more relatable, there are no perfect victims. <br/><br/>The book is fairly short, but it did drag at times, especially when J</span>
  <span id="freeText1318654566581077534" style="display:none">2.5 STARS<br /><br />"Her worst nightmare is realized and she finds herself on the run with her two young children, no money, and no plan." While this did happen in the book, there's a lot that happened before this, and even more story that happens after. Jillian herself is drawn fairly realistically. She isn't perfect, she's selfish at times, she doesn't always put her kids first. It made her more relatable, there are no perfect victims. <br /><br />The book is fairly short, but it did drag at times, especially when Jillian is hand-wringing. I loved it when her mother and her friend gave her some "snap out of it!" tough love.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[There were things that didn't seem all that believable, and those took me out of the story:<br />1) Pregnant women who are only two months along don't have bulging bellies, especially not that other people notice!<br />2) If you disappear from work and are arrested for a felony, your boss isn't going to beg you to take your job back.<br />3) Just because a lawyer from work is your friend, is he really going to drop everything to defend you against felony charges and represent you in family court so you can regain custody? Is he even the right lawyer to do that? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />The ending was really out there, for as smart as Gordon was throughout the book, he seemed struck by stupidity.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1318654566581077534" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
