<div id="review_1738570284" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1738570284" />
    <a title="Miranda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38940444-miranda"><img alt="Miranda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420767815p2/38940444.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1738570284?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Miranda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Miranda" href="/user/show/38940444-miranda">Miranda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1738570284" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6585387336282292253">Let me start by saying, I don’t usually “review” books. I try to rate them if I think about it, but I don’t leave reviews. But, this book deserves it. From the moment I started reading, I was hooked. As you can see, it only took me 48 hours to read, while working two different jobs, so every minute of free time I have had the past couple days, was spent engrossed in this story. When I wasn’t reading it, I was thinking about it. I felt that the plot was very relatable. The author did a wonderful </span>
  <span id="freeText6585387336282292253" style="display:none">Let me start by saying, I don’t usually “review” books. I try to rate them if I think about it, but I don’t leave reviews. But, this book deserves it. From the moment I started reading, I was hooked. As you can see, it only took me 48 hours to read, while working two different jobs, so every minute of free time I have had the past couple days, was spent engrossed in this story. When I wasn’t reading it, I was thinking about it. I felt that the plot was very relatable. The author did a wonderful job depicting an abusive relationship, while not making me question if it could truly happen. Kept me on the edge of my seat wondering what would happen next. Would recommend ten times over. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6585387336282292253" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
